@node "Introduction" "Introduction         "

 @{b}Introduction@{ub}


 You ask yourself why another FileManager?

 It's easy, I don't like the concept of Directory Opus 5 very much,  and
 Directory Opus 4 is too slow with scanning directories.

 And when I look at a new freeware or  shareware  FileManager,  I  don't
 find what I want.

 So, I decided to make my own, with all the features that I  want,  like
 Popup-Menus!



 @{i}@{u}Features of FileQuest:@{ui}@{uu}

 o OS 2.04 and more.

 o Popup-menus!

 o Needs only 230KB of memory (without screen).

 o Identifies FileTypes without an external library.

 o Everything is configurable (Buttons, PopupMenus, FileTypes...).

 o An external Configuration program!

 o Uses the @{"bgui.library" link "bgui.library" 0}.

 o 2 to 10 times the speed of DOPUS 4 (dir, copy..).

 o 5 banks of 5 drives.

 o Permanent list of Devices/Volumes and Assigns.

 o 2 banks of 32 action-buttons.

 o Localised.

 o Uses the @{"screennotify.library" link "screennotify.library" 0} if present.
   (when FileQuest is on the Workbench).
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation         "

 @{b}Installation@{ub}


 @{i}o @{u}Automatic installation@{ui}@{uu}

    Just click on the Install_English icon, and answer the questions.


 @{i}o @{u}Manual installation@{ui}@{uu}


    Just copy the FileQuest directory and create a  'FileQuest:'  assign
    to it.


    @{u}The ideal tree is:@{uu}

        @{b}FileQuest/ (Dir.)@{ub}

            FileQuest
            FileQuest.info

            @{b}Config/ (Dir.)@{ub}

                ConfigFileQuest
                ConfigFileQuest.info

                FileQuest.FileTypes
                FileQuest.Prefs
                FileQuest.PopupMenu


    FileQuest searches for its config-file in @{fg shine}FileQuest:Config/@{fg text}, and  if
    it is not found there, FileQuest searches in @{fg shine}S:@{fg text}.

    FileQuest also searches for its  configurator  in  @{fg shine}FileQuest:Config/@{fg text}
    and after that, in FileQuest:.

    Ensure that you have the suitable version of @{"bgui.library" link "bgui.library" 0} in Libs:.
@endnode

@node "FileQuest_Icon" "Icon               "

 @{b}Icon@{ub}


 You can set all these parameters in the tooltypes, or specify  them  on
 the command line:


 @{fg shine}CX_POPKEY@{fg text}          Hotkey for popup GUI.
                    (default: CONTROL ALT F).

 @{fg shine}CX_PRIORITY@{fg text}        Priority of Hotkey.
                    (default: 1).

 @{fg shine}CX_POPUP@{fg text}           Popup GUI at start?
                    (default: YES).


 @{fg shine}APPICON@{fg text}            Place an @{"AppIcon" link "AppIcon" 0} on the Workbench?
                    (default: YES).
@endnode

@node "FileQuest_GUI" "GUI"

 @{b}GUI of FileQuest@{ub}


 @{u}The GUI comprises:@{uu}


 o Two lists for displaying directories.

 o Above  each list,  a button that displays the name of current volume and
   the available space on it.

   When you click on it, it loads the @{"PARENT" link "PARENT" 0}
   directory into the current list.


 o Below this, there are action-buttons (2 banks).

 o In the middle of the window, beginning at the top:

    - The @{"<->" link "SWAP" 0} button allows you to swap lists.

    - 5 banks of drives, organized into configurable themes that can  be
      changed using the PopCycle gadget or the Right Mouse Button.

    - The list of Device, Volumes and Assigns. You can cycle through the
      contents using the PopCycle gadget or the Right Mouse Button.

    - The "Update" button updates the current list of  devices,  volumes
      or assigns.


 @{b}The mouse@{ub}


 o @{fg shine}On the directory list@{fg text}

    When you click the Right Mouse Button, on the active directory list,
    it activates the @{"POPUP-MENU" link "ConfigGUI_POPMENU" 0}.


 o @{fg shine}On drive banks@{fg text}

    When you click  the  Right  Mouse  Button,  it  cycles  through  the
    different drive banks.


 o @{fg shine}On the list of Devices, Volumes and Assigns@{fg text}

    When you click the Right Mouse Button, it cycles through  the  three
    types of lists.
@endnode

@node "AppIcon" "AppIcon             "

 @{b}AppIcon@{ub}


 When you drop a file or a directory on the AppIcon, you can:


    - Add a default icon.

 or

    - Perform an action on the file, according to its FileType.


 See also @{"Icon" link "FileQuest_Icon" 0}.
@endnode

@node "KeyBoard" "KeyBoard"

 @{b}Shortcut Keys:@{ub}



 @{fg shine}TAB or SPACE@{fg text}          Activate the other list.

 @{fg shine}SHIFT+SPACE@{fg text}           Cycle drive banks.

 @{fg shine}CONTROL+SPACE@{fg text}         Cycle list of Devices/Volumes/Assigns.

 @{fg shine}ALT+SPACE@{fg text}             Cycle Action button banks

 @{fg shine}BACK-SPACE@{fg text}            Read Parent directory.

 @{fg shine}RETURN@{fg text}                Activate the string gadget of current dir.

 @{fg shine}Key "1" to "5"@{fg text}        Activate drive number <x> of current bank.


 @{u}IMPORTANT:@{uu}

 The character underlined in any Action button can  be  used  to  select
 that button via the keyboard.
@endnode

