@node "ConfigGUI" "GUI"

 @{b}Configurator GUI@{ub}


 @{u}The Configurator GUI is made up of 7 pages:@{uu}


 @{" GUI        " link "ConfigGUI_GUI" 0} : Screen, GUI, Fonts...

 @{" Buttons    " link "ConfigGUI_BUTTON" 0} : Action buttons.

 @{" Drives     " link "ConfigGUI_DRIVE" 0} : Banks of drives or directories.

 @{" Popup menu " link "ConfigGUI_POPMENU" 0} : Popup menu.

 @{" FileTypes  " link "ConfigGUI_FILETYPE" 0} : FileType management.

 @{" Systems    " link "ConfigGUI_SYSTEM" 0} : Select colors, ouput window...

 @{" Misc       " link "ConfigGUI_MISC" 0} : Startup directory...



 @{u}And other windows:@{uu}


 @{" Commands list      " link "Win.ListCommand" 0}

 @{" Arguments list     " link "Win.ArgList" 0}

 @{" Flags list         " link "Win.Options" 0}

 @{" Painter window     " link "Win.Painter" 0}
@endnode

@node "ConfigGUI_BUTTON" "Buttons    "

 @{b}Buttons Page@{ub}


 This page is made up of 2 parts:

 - Command

 - Buttons



 1 - @{u}The 'Command' group@{uu}

    From the top downwards:


    @{i}o @{fg shine}Name of button@{ui}@{fg text}

        In the "@{fg shine}Name@{fg text}" string gadget you  can  enter
        the text that will be displayed inside the button.

        If there is a '@{fg shine}_@{fg text}' character in the button
        name, the character following it will be a shortcut key:

        Re@{fg shine}_@{fg text}ad : The 'a' key will select this button.


    @{i}o @{fg shine}Enter a command@{ui}@{fg text}

        The  Cycle  gadget  'Command/CLI'  allows you to define the type of
        command that can be entered to the right of the cycle gadget.


        When you click on the select button (between  the  cycle  and  the
        string gadget):


        o Command

            It opens a window with the list of internal  commands.
            Remove or set arguments of them.


        o CLI

            It opens a file-requester that allows you to select an AmigaDOS
            program.

            In  this mode you can give the external program some arguments,
            such as the selected file.



    o @{fg shine}2 CheckBox Gadgets@{fg text}

        The  first  allows  you  to open the Flags window and the other the
        Painter window.


 2 - @{u}The 'Buttons' group@{uu}

    From the top downwards:


    o @{fg shine}The 'Line' slider@{fg text}

        Lets you select the line of buttons to edit (5 lines per bank).


    o @{fg shine}8 buttons@{fg text}

        Lets you define all the buttons on the current line.


    o @{fg shine}The 'Bank' slider@{fg text}

        Lets you define buttons for the first or second bank.
@endnode

@node "ConfigGUI_DRIVE" "Drives   "

 @{b}Drives Page@{ub}


 This page is made up of 3 groups:

 - Bank

 - Drive

 - Others



 1 - @{u}The 'Bank' group@{uu}

    This group is made up of 2 gadgets: a slider to choose one of the  5
    banks, and a string gadget to enter a name for this bank.



 2 - @{u}The 'Drive' group@{uu}

    In this group, you can define drives for the current bank.

    With the label string gadget you can enter a  name  for  the  drive,
    below  it  you  can  choose the drive or directory to scan when this
    button is selected.

    Colors of each drive button can be modified with the Painter Window.


 3 - @{u}The 'Others' group@{uu}

    These 4 buttons are here to configure the colors of these  FileQuest
    gadgets:


    @{fg shine}<->@{fg text}:        In FileQuest, it's the SWAP button.

    @{fg shine}Bank1@{fg text}:      In FileQuest, it's the Drive-bank selector.

    @{fg shine}Device@{fg text}:     In FileQuest, it's the List selector. (Dev/Vol/Ass).

    @{fg shine}Update@{fg text}:     In FileQuest, it's the 'Update' gadget for list of device...
@endnode

@node "ConfigGUI_GUI" "GUI Page        "

 @{b}GUI Page@{ub}


 This is made up of 3 groups:

 - Screen

 - Fonts

 - GUI Look



 1 - @{u}Screen setup@{uu}

     The PopCycle gadget allows you to choose the  type  of  screen  for
     FileQuest:


     - @{i}@{fg shine}On Workbench@{ui}@{fg text} :     FileQuest will open its window on the Workbench
                          screen.
                          The size of its window can be set up in the @{"System" link "ConfigGUI_SYSTEM" 0}
                          page.


     - @{i}@{fg shine}Like Workbench@{ui}@{fg text} :   FileQuest open a screen with the same size, mode
                          of the Workbench. Colors can be changed with the
                          @{i}@{fg shine}Palette@{ui}@{fg text} gadget.

     - @{i}@{fg shine}Custom Screen@{ui}@{fg text} :    FileQuest open a custom screen, which can be set up
                          with the button @{i}@{fg shine}Screen Mode@{ui}@{fg text} below the listview.
                          Colors can be changed with the @{i}@{fg shine}Palette@{ui}@{fg text} gadget.



     The @{fg shine}Backdrop@{fg text} CheckBox gadget lets you  to  put  FileQuest's  window
     into backdrop mode.

     The Palette button lets you redefine the colors of the screen.


 2 - @{u}Fonts setup@{uu}

    The 'Choose font' button opens an ASL font-requester to  select  the
    font for the 'Screen/Window', 'Dir Lists' or 'Gadgets'.


 3 - @{u}GUI Look@{uu}

    This group is made up of many PopCycle gadgets:


    o @{fg shine}Aspect@{fg text}

        3 possibilities:

        - @{i}@{fg shine}Auto@{ui}@{fg text}                  Gadget frames will be THIN or THICK
                                according to the screen aspect-ratio.
        - @{i}@{fg shine}Thin@{ui}@{fg text}                  Gadget frames will be in THIN mode.
        - @{i}@{fg shine}Thick@{ui}@{fg text}                 Gadget frames will be in THICK mode.


    o @{fg shine}Frames@{fg text}

        2 possibilities:

        - @{i}@{fg shine}Standard@{ui}@{fg text}              Gadget frames look normal.
        - @{i}@{fg shine}XEN@{ui}@{fg text}                   Gadget frames will be in XEN mode.


    o @{fg shine}Refresh@{fg text}

        2 possibilities:

        - @{i}@{fg shine}SmartRefresh@{ui}@{fg text}          The window will be in SmartRefresh mode.

        - @{i}@{fg shine}SimpleRefresh@{ui}@{fg text}         The window will be in SimpleRefresh mode.


    o @{fg shine}Scroller@{fg text}

        2 possibilities:

        - @{i}@{fg shine}Normal@{ui}@{fg text}                Color of scroller will be black.
        - @{i}@{fg shine}New Look@{ui}@{fg text}              Color of scroller will be white.


    o @{fg shine}Requesters@{fg text}

        3 possibilities:

        - @{i}@{fg shine}Center Screen@{ui}@{fg text}         Open in the middle of the screen.
        - @{i}@{fg shine}Center Mouse@{ui}@{fg text}          Open under the mouse.
        - @{i}@{fg shine}TopLeft@{ui}@{fg text}               Open in the top-left corner.


    o @{fg shine}Drawing mode@{fg text}

        2 possibilities:

        - @{i}@{fg shine}With Buffer@{ui}@{fg text}           Use a buffer for drawing. The display will be
                                done as a block.


        - @{i}@{fg shine}No Buffer@{ui}@{fg text}             Draw directly on window, necessary for
                                Graphics-cards under emulation.
@endnode

@node "ConfigGUI_POPMENU" "Popup menus"

 @{b}Popup-Menu Page@{ub}


 This page is made up of 3 groups:

 - 2 CheckBox Gadgets

 - A 'Command' group

 - An 'Items' group.



 1 - @{u}CheckBoxes@{uu}

    The 'Enable PopupMenu' enables or disables the use of Popup Menus.

    The 'Flags' checkbox lets you open the Flags window.


 2 - @{u}The 'Command'  group@{uu}

    In this group, we have:


    @{i}o @{fg shine}Name of item@{ui}@{fg text}

        In the "Name" string gadget you can enter the  item  label  that
        will be displayed in PopupMenu.


    @{i}o @{fg shine}Enter Command@{ui}@{fg text}

        The Cycle gadget 'Command/CLI' lets you define the type of  command
        that can be entered to the right of the cycle gadget.

        When you click on the select button (between the cycle  and  the
        string gadget):


        o Command

            Opens a window with a list of internal commands.  Remove  or
            set arguments for them.


        o CLI

            Opens a file-requester that allows you to select an AmigaDOS
            program.

            In  this  mode  you  can  give  the  external  program  some
            arguments, such as the selected file.



 3 - @{u}The 'Items' group@{uu}

    This group contains a ListView, in which  all  items  of  the  Popup
    Menus are listed.

    Below that, we have:

    o @{fg shine}New@{fg text}          Create a new item.

    o @{fg shine}Delete@{fg text}       Delete the current item.

    o @{fg shine}Up@{fg text}           Move the current item up.

    o @{fg shine}Down@{fg text}         Move the current item down.
@endnode

@node "ConfigGUI_FILETYPE" "FileTypes  "

 @{b}FileTypes Page@{ub}

 This page is made up of 2 groups:

 - The 'Command' group

 - The 'FileTypes' group


 1 - @{u}The 'Command' group@{uu}

    o @{i}@{fg shine}Mode 'Double Click' or 'Click and Click'@{ui}@{fg text}

        Allows you to configure an action when  you  'Double  Click'  or
        'Click And Click'.
        'Click and 'Click' means selecting  a  file  or  dir,  and  then
        clicking on the other list.


    o @{i}@{fg shine}Enter command@{ui}@{fg text}

        The Cycle gadget 'Command/CLI'  allow  to  define  the  type  of
        command who can be enter on the right of the cycle gadget.


        When you click on the select button (between the cycle  and  the
        string gadget):


        o Command

            Opens a window with a list of internal commands.  Remove  or
            set arguments for them.


        o CLI

            Opens a file-requester that allows you to select an AmigaDOS
            program.

            In  this  mode  you  can  give  the  external  program  some
            arguments, such as the selected file..


    o @{i}@{fg shine}The 'Flags' checkBox'@{ui}@{fg text}

        Lets you open the Flags window.


 2 - @{u}The 'FileTypes' group@{uu}


    o @{i}@{fg shine}The listview@{ui}@{fg text}

        This list contains all the FileTypes that have been entered. You
        can enter the name of a FileType in the string gadget below this
        list.


    o @{i}@{fg shine}Type of FileType@{ui}@{fg text}

        This cycle gadget lets you choose the method  of  recognising  a
        file-type.  The  data  for the recognition can be entered in the
        string gadget to the right of this cycle gadget.


        @{i}Pattern@{ui}:    The recognition of the file will be done via the name of
                    the file, usually its extension.

                    eg: "#?.guide" this type will apply to all files who have
                    ".guide" at the end of their name.

        @{i}Bytes@{ui}:     This method is more precise, because it reads the
                    header of the file:

                    "?" is an unknown byte.

                    If "$" is the first character, data must be entered in
                    hexadecimal.

                    Eg: ??-lh?-       : The header of an Lha file.
                        FORM????ILBM  : The header of an IFF-ILBM file
                                        (Picture).

                        $?? 03 F3     : The header of an AmigaDOS executable.




    o @{i}@{fg shine}Operations on the items list@{ui}@{fg text}

        o @{fg shine}New@{fg text}          Create a new item.

        o @{fg shine}Delete@{fg text}       Delete the current item.

        o @{fg shine}Up@{fg text}           Move the current item up.

        o @{fg shine}Down@{fg text}         Move the current item down.
@endnode

@node "ConfigGUI_SYSTEM" "System      "

 @{b}The System Page@{ub}


 This page is made up of 3 groups:

 - Dir lists

 - Window

 - Output window


 1 - @{u}The 'Dir lists' group@{uu}

    This group begins with a string gadget that allows you to  configure
    the indentation between the filename and its size.


    And after that some buttons that allow you to configure  the  colors
    of  different elements of the lists of dirs/files, such as the color
    of the select-bar, colors of directories, etc.



 2 - @{u}The 'Window' group@{uu}

    In this group, you can configure the size of the  FileQuest  window.
    With the PopCycle gadget, the window can fill the whole screen or if
    set to 'Set Size' you can set  the  size  manually  (with  the  'Set
    manual' button).


 3 - @{u}The 'Output window' group@{uu}

    With this, you can configure the FileQuest output window  used  when
    CLI commands are executed.
@endnode

@node "ConfigGUI_MISC" "Misc.     "

 @{b}Misc. page@{ub}


 There's only one group:

 - Startup dir



 1 - @{u}The 'Startup dir' group@{uu}

    Lets you choose the directory that will be scanned  when  you  start
    FileQuest.
@endnode

