@node "Win.ListCommand" "List of commands window            "

 @{b}'List of commands' window@{ub}


 This window lists all the internal command and their options.

 When you click on one, the selected command will  be  inserted  in  the
 command string gadget.
@endnode

@node "Win.ArgList" "List of arguments window            "

 @{b}'List of arguments' windows@{ub}


 This window lists the arguments that can be used with CLI commands. Use
 of multiple arguments in the command line is allowed.


 @{u}@{fg shine}{a}            All selected files (no path), desel.@{uu}@{fg text}

 This  argument  is  replaced  in  the  command  line  by  all  selected
 files/dirs, but without their pathname.

 You must use the "CD Source" option.


 @{b}IMPORTANT@{ub}:

    - Files/Dirs will be quoted.

    - Entries will be automatically deselected.



 @{u}@{fg shine}{c}            Last clicked file@{uu}@{fg text}

 The argument will be replaced by the last Clicked-File, without path.

 You must use the "CD Source" option of use the {d} argument.


 "{d}{c}" = Name of file with its path.

 @{b}IMPORTANT@{ub}:

    - File will not be quoted (you can use "{c}" or "{d}{c}").

 

 @{u}@{fg shine}{d}            Source@{uu}@{fg text}

 This argument will be replaced by the path of the source window.



 @{u}@{fg shine}{D}            Destination@{uu}@{fg text}

 This argument will be replaced by the path of the destination window.



 @{u}@{fg shine}{f}            All selected files with path, desel.@{uu}@{fg text}

 Like the {a} argument but with the path.

 The {a} parameter is better in most cases.



 @{u}@{fg shine}{F}            First selected file.@{uu}@{fg text}

 This argument will replaced by the first selected entry.

 It is often used with the 'Run on each file" option,  for  CLI-Commands
 that cannot handle multiple file/dirs as parameters.

 @{b}IMPORTANT@{ub}:

    - File/dirs. are not quoted.

    - Entry does not include the path.

    - Entry is not automatically deselected (see flags window).



 @{u}@{fg shine}{P}            PubScreen name@{uu}@{fg text}

 This argument is replaced with the name of PublicScreen of FileQuest.



 @{u}@{fg shine}{s"Title"}     Request a string@{uu}@{fg text}

 This argument asks for a string. If the one is entered, the argument is
 replaced by it.


 "Title"    Title of string gadget.

 You can include a default text for the string gadget:

 {s"Title":"Default"}
@endnode

@node "Win.Options" "Flags window               "

 @{b}'List of flags' window@{ub}


 Thin window contain all options that can accompany a command.


 @{u}@{fg shine}Run on each file@{uu}@{fg text}

    This flag launches the command with each entry, one at a time.

    It should always be  used  with  the  argument  "@{fg shine}{F}@{fg text}"  because  that
    deselects  the  first  file,  so  at  the next launch it will be the
    second entry that will be passed as the argument.


 @{u}@{fg shine}Output window@{uu}@{fg text}

    Opens an output window for the command, as  defined  on  the  System
    Page in ConfigFileQuest.



 @{u}@{fg shine}Rescan source@{uu}@{fg text}

    Re-reads the source directory @{b}after@{ub} the launch of the command.



 @{u}@{fg shine}Rescan dest.@{uu}@{fg text}

    Re-reads the destination directory @{b}after@{ub} the launch of the command.



 @{u}@{fg shine}ReSort source@{uu}@{fg text}

    Re-sorts the source directory @{b}after@{ub} the launch of the command.



 @{u}@{fg shine}ReSort dest.@{uu}@{fg text}

    Re-sorts the destination directory @{b}after@{ub} the launch of the command.


 @{u}@{fg shine}CD source@{uu}@{fg text}

    Changes to the source directory before launching the command.

    With this flag there is no need to pass the entries' path. (@{fg shine}{d}@{fg text}).



 @{u}@{fg shine}CD destination@{uu}@{fg text}

    Changes to  the  desination  directory  before  the  launch  of  the
    command.

    With this flag there is no need to pass the entries' path. (@{fg shine}{D}@{fg text}).
@endnode

@node "Win.Painter" "Painter window"

 @{b}'Painter' window@{ub}


 This window contains 4 palettes for choosing gadget colors.

 The colors are pen, back pen, fill and back fill.
@endnode

@node "bgui.library" "bgui.library"

 @{b}La bgui.library@{ub}


 BGUI allows you to easily create and manage  font  sensitive  and  size
 adjustable GUI's.

 For the user, it allows you to have smaller programs with nice GUI's.


 @{u}Features:@{uu}

 - Relatively small size

 - Font sensitive

 - Supports resizeable windows.

 - Free of charge (giftware), non-crippled

 - Normal or XEN look

 - Many type of frames

 - Thin, Thick or Automatic gadget border
@endnode

@node "screennotify.library" "screennotify.library"

 @{b}La ScreenNotify.library@{ub}


 The ScreenNotify.library is (C) 1995-1996 Stefan Becker.

 The complete archive is available on Aminet:util/libs/ScreenNotify10.lha, or
 on the Amiga CD 6.
@endnode

